      <h1>Bugs &amp; Drugs — Terms of Use &amp; Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="bd-terms__date"><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Educational use only</h2>
      <p>Bugs &amp; Drugs is a clinical decision <strong>support</strong> tool intended for use by licensed healthcare professionals. The content is informational and educational only. It is <strong>not</strong> medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment, and it does <strong>not</strong> establish a clinician–patient relationship between Dosys Health LLC, PharmacyNews.ai, and any user or patient.</p>

      <h2>2. Prescriber responsibility</h2>
      <p>The prescriber is solely responsible for verifying every dose, drug choice, route, and duration against authoritative sources (FDA prescribing information, current published guidelines, the institutional formulary, and the patient's complete clinical picture) before issuing any prescription or administration order. Bugs &amp; Drugs displays paraphrased excerpts and structured summaries of published guidelines and FDA labels. It does not replace, override, or warrant those sources.</p>

      <h2>3. No warranty</h2>
      <p>The information on Bugs &amp; Drugs is provided "as is" without any warranty, express or implied, including warranties of accuracy, completeness, currency, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. Guidelines, FDA labels, and antimicrobial resistance patterns change frequently. The site may not reflect the most recent guideline revision, label update, drug approval, or safety alert. Users should always confirm against the original source.</p>

      <h2>4. Calculator output</h2>
      <p>The dose calculator uses validated formulas (Cockcroft-Gault for adult creatinine clearance; bedside Schwartz for pediatric) and FDA-label-derived renal-adjustment buckets. Output is a <em>starting-point</em> recommendation and may not be appropriate for an individual patient because of factors not captured by the inputs (allergies, drug interactions, hepatic function, organ-specific PK considerations, fluid status, dialysis modality, augmented renal clearance, obesity at extremes, pregnancy, critical illness, neonatal status, and others). Users must independently confirm the recommendation, adjust for the individual patient, and verify against the FDA label.</p>

      <h2>5. No PHI</h2>
      <p>Do not enter Protected Health Information (PHI) or any patient-identifying information into the dose calculator or any other input on this site. Calculator inputs are not stored on the server. The calculator endpoint sets <code>Cache-Control: no-store</code>. We make no representation that interactions are encrypted or HIPAA-compliant for PHI.</p>

